column5: Great Report Joey...  Awesome pictures... were still up at camp, ill have a nice report tonite or tomorrow...  Glad to see ya all had a great time!!

Yeah that bird is a 'Common Flicker' considered part of woodpecker family.  Looks like a good time was had by all!  Really like the campfire video w/ the music kinda like tunes from the 30's. Thanks for posting.
the bird is a Medowlark
Great report and pics Joey  It's good to see that there was a good turn around and that everyone had a good time.  Love the view of the cabin  Thanks for sharing Leechman
Hey Joey, Nice job on the report and the campfire video was really cool.. It was nice to see everyone again and hopefully this fall G2G will become part of our traditional Lakair get togethers.
Great report Joey.  Was good to see you folks again for a bit this past Friday.   I suspect Paul didn't get his musky either.   Next year .. just wait until next year.   I say that all the time.
thanks for the report, some nice pics!
Ah right on Joey... Love the pics and report.  Glad I finally got to meet you and Paul!!  You're way hotter in person!!  HD
Looks like a blast Joey! Too bad the fishes didn't want to come out and play though. Like you said, spending a day fishing with Lew would be worth the admission fee anyways!
Crikey Joey.  That was HUGE with pics.  Thanks for that.  I was wondering how many went blind from the Moonshine?

Thanks for all the responses everyone.  I'm still replaying the fun we had up there in my head.  Work was brutal and so was traffic today so reality has set in once again  Drew, there were a few blind mice and that's all I gotta say about that  Joey
Thanx for the pics and the report.Wish I was there. Joe

Wow what an outstanding report Joey you put your heart into those reports thanks for taking the long time it takes to put that together. Excellent shots of the sun. Too bad Paul forgot all those clothes guess you went shopping lol.  Boy was Roy having a bad hair day or what  I always enjoy your reports girl
Very nice report Joey, was definately a pleasure meeting you and even better sharing a boat with ya.  Even though the fishing was slow, I had a very good time up there meeting everybody.
Great report Joey.
Great Report Joey!  Looks like everyone had a blast even though the fishing wasn't the best!
nice report Joey looks like a great time was had wish there were some more pics to get a better feel of the outting
GREAT REPORT Joey....really cool pics, that looks like fun and then some. Had me chucklin' at a few of the pics....and i especially like the ' Lew 'O'clock' expression.
Excellent report and pics Joey!!!  It was great sharing the cabin with you, Paul and Leslie!!!  That report really captured the trip for me!
Looks like you all had a wonderful time up at Lakair. Great report.
Great report! The bird is a flicker, they eat ants and stuff.  Darren
Thank you Darren  Joey

Well I'd say you had a great week's vacation...enjoyed reading this and nice pics as well.  Love GCD's hat.  I was going to say that the bird was a partridge...or maybe a flicker is the same thing...but what do I know.  haha

Great wrap-up of the week Joey, thanks !!  Always good spending time with you guys and I was really sorry that I had to leave 4 days early, but as you know I had things to take care of, but thankfully, everything worked out well.  Looks like I missed out on a good party on Saturday night, unfortunately.  Really enjoyed fishing with you, it was just unfortunate that those darned winds kept us from fishing those islands we headed for, but we'll get one of those big girls next June  Roger & I had the same problems with the winds on Friday morning.  Here's a good shot of you just before you landed the paddle  See you guys in November.

Great report Joey! I wondered if Chris snuck away for the weekend, things were pretty quite here in London. That's a pretty rare photo of Roy without a hat on! Glen told me that Roy even wears his hat in the shower... I'm not sure how Glen would know. hmmmm I'm sorry I couldn't be there, it looked like "all y'all" had fun! -Brian
wow.......great report  almost like being there
Great report Joey, glad everyone had a good time...sorry I couldn't make it  Thanks for taking the time to post all those pics  Maureen

Awesome report! I had an amazing time and it all went by too fast! It was great meeting so many of you and I look forward to the next hurrah. Fishing was tough for us as well....with about 3 days of fishing averaging 8 hours a day on the water, i only managed 8 or 9 fish. Glen's skunk hat is priceless! That jam footage is hilarious as well......only after imbibing numerous shots of moonshine would I ever play Yngwie Malmsteen arpeggio sweeps over a slow blues jam! Thanks to everyone that kept me in the sauce on Saturday night! And now, it's back to work.
Look like another fantastic get together, thanks for the report...
What a super report Joey  All those pics are great.......Looks like everyone had a blast!
Thanks for a great report Joey. Looks like I missed a good one. I was looking forward to being there, however had to cancel due to a business trip that came up.
Great report Joey!  Looked like another classic Lakair G2G for sure!  Some amazing pictures and some pretty cool jamming in that video...those guys can play!
Thanks for that Joey.  Needs more pics!   Great to hear some nice playin' with chatter at the fire too.
looks like a great time had by all congrants
Super report, wish I could have made it up for that one looked like a great time ..  Oh well... Bring on the BOQ
thanks for the report Joey! we had a good time despite resorting to tiny hooks and worms to catch a few small perch  great meeting all you..
WOW......That is a great report,thanx for sharing!!  a 72incher (must be a PB...LOL)  cheers Streamerguy
